AB  - This paper is a theoretical study of the determination of prices, interest rates and currency exchange rates, set in an infinitely-lived two-country world which is subject both to stochastic endowment shocks and to monetary instability. Formulas are obtained for pricing all equity claims, nominally-denominated bonds, and currencies, and these formulas are related to earlier, closely related results in the theories of money, finance international trade.
